    <div class="volunteer">
      <img src="img/volunteer.jpg" alt="volunteer" />
      <h2>Volunteer in Africa</h2>
      <div class="volunteer_info">
        <p>
          Are you looking for a way to make a difference in the world, gain new
          experiences and training, see new career possibilities, do something
          different, get away from the normal grind, be adventurous, share your
          faith, or have you always had a secret desire to see Africa? We can
          help you achieve any and all of those goals.
        </p>
        <p>
          Dolphin Foundation is located in the beautiful, East African city of
          Kampala, Uganda. Dolphin Foundation Uganda, Inc., is a registered NGO
          in Uganda. We care for abandoned, orphaned and at risk babies. Over
          three hundred babies have found love and life at the Dolphin baby
          home. We need all kinds of talents, from film making, painting,
          teaching, building, physical therapy and nursing to just holding and
          cuddling babies who need lots love.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can volunteer for up to one month. A one to two week stay is
          recommended. After all, this is Africa and it will require a lot of
          adjustment on your part. (To volunteer for longer than one month will
          require evaluation and approval from the Dolphin Foundation
          directors.)
        </p>
        <p>
          As a volunteer Dolphin Foundation becomes your sponsor to stay in the
          country and Dolphin is responsible for you and your activities while
          in Uganda. Volunteers may only stay in our housing on campus. Only
          volunteers living on campus in our volunteer program may volunteer at
          Dolphin Foundation. We have a large volunteer program and day visitors
          are not allowed to volunteer.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your volunteer housing payments must state they are for your housing.
          All checks or donations must state your name and “Housing Payment.” If
          not we might use it for formula!!
        </p>
        <p>
          All volunteers over the age of 18 are required to purchase a volunteer
          visa, regardless of their length of stay, unless you have been
          otherwise instructed by the volunteer coordinator. The volunteer Visa
          will cost $200 to $250, depending on where you are coming from. After
          you have applied to volunteer at Dolphin Foundation and have received
          permission from our volunteer coordinator to plan your trip and come,
          you will receive additional instructions about getting your volunteer
          visa.
        </p>
        <p>
          Volunteers must be at least 18 years of age or be accompanied by a
          parent or guardian.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="volunteer_info">
        <h3>What we provide our volunteers:</h3>
        <p>
          Accommodations in an inexpensive ($750 US dollars per month. If
          staying less than one month, the price is $30 per night), spacious and
          beautiful volunteer house separate from the baby home, but within the
          Dolphin Foundation compound, with all the charm that is Africa and
          only a one minute walk to the baby home. Provided: Washing Machine,
          dryer, microwave, stove, fridge, bedding, towels, etc.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your volunteer housing payments must state they are for your housing.
          Any checks must have your name and “Housing Payment” on the check or
          the donation form. If not it might be used for formula!!
        </p>
        <p>
          Our volunteer house has a cook and cleaning lady Monday thru Friday.
          Safina is a great cook and will provide your breakfast and the evening
          meal. Ritha helps in the kitchen and does most of the cleaning. We
          have a varied menu which includes eggs, toast, cinnamon rolls, etc.
          for breakfast, and stew, hamburgers and frys, spaghetti, etc. for
          dinner. The morning chai and mid-day meal are provided while on duty
          at Dolphin, but snacks and eating out are on your own. Most volunteers
          spend about $150 to $200 for extra food and eating out per month.
          Remember it is Africa and many of our meals at Dolphin are African
          style, rice and beans, ugali and vegetables and luscious fruit. There
          are many good restaurants in Kampala.
        </p>
        <p>Training, supervision and support are also provided.</p>
        <p>
          Driver and transportation is provided while on duty at Dolphin. Some
          volunteers use the inexpensive taxi (minivans) for personal trips to
          town. Boda Boda (motorcycle taxis) are strongly advised against.
        </p>
        <p>
          Safe, secure grounds with an electric fenced yard and 24 hour guards
          on the property. Get in Touch
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="volunteer_info">
        <h3>Get in Touch</h3>
        <p>
          If you are interested send an email to:
          <span style="color: blue">fionambabzi@gmail.com</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="volunteer_info">
        <h3>How to Apply</h3>
        <p>
          To apply to volunteer at Dolphin Foundation you will send in your
          application to
          <span style="color: blue">fionambabzi@gmail.com</span> then wait for
          your application and dates to be approved. If you do not receive a
          return email within 2 weeks, remember it is Africa, and try again.
          Once you are approved you will send in a $100 deposit which will hold
          your bed space in the volunteer house. You will not be reserved to
          volunteer at Dolphin until the $100 deposit is made. Wanting to come
          is not the same thing as coming!
        </p>
        <p>
          After being approved to volunteer and after we receive your $100
          deposit, you will receive a copy of our Volunteer Handbook. When you
          return the liability and medical release forms, you must also return
          the signed agreement that you have read and understood the volunteer
          handbook.
        </p>
        <p>
          Any checks or payments made for your volunteer housing must state your
          name and “housing payment”. If not it might be used to buy formula!!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
